cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.MM. 

The paper deals with document analysis, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a modular architecture, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper utilizes both visual and textual content, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible sub-category.
